<br>
Good post, I didn't know about the cap, so that's useful information.<br>
<br>
However, you have all missed the best setup, although a little bit of a pain.<br>
<br>
We know that melees regularly swap weapons, depending on the situation, or after getting a particular proc.<br>
<br>
Well, for those of us with both shawls (I have neither =( ), the correct answer is to set up hotkeys for hot swapping the shrouds.  When you are going to cast, use the ODS (saves mana), when not casting, swap in the 8th shawl (more mana regen to quickly replace whatever you just used).<br>
<br>
Edit - Oh yeah, if the spell being cast is a buff, then I guess you would keep the 8th shawl, 15% extra duration &gt; 10% mana savings, except for some special circumstances.<br>
<br>
Oh yeah, another question for you Aerillea (or whoever might know):<br>
<br>
How does Affliction Efficiency factor into this?  That's a 25% mana savings on DoTs right there.  Does that preclude ANY other savings (SCM, spec, focus), or is the Affliction Efficiency considered separately from &quot;Mana Conservation&quot;, per se.<br>
