<blockquote type=cite><blockquote><hr>"We need to make sure everything is working properly before we can patch this stuff -Alan "<hr></blockquote></blockquote></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaerillea.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerillea</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 220<br> <font color=#333399>(6/10/02 4:30:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26371.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: O. Death Shroud vs. 8th shawl</span><hr size=1> Anything can feel like it's giving you more mana, but unless you actually test it with numbers, you can't say it does a thing.<br>
<br>
<br>
Specialization: Evocation<br>
<br>
Test 1 <br>
Without the Focus item, see how many times you can cast the spell.  Record this number.  Use wildfire or Moonfire and record how many times you can cast it.  <br>
<br>
Test 2<br>
With the Focus item, see how many times you can cast the spell.  Record this number.<br>
<br>
When casting the spells, the spell must be cast right after they refresh.<br>
<br>
If you fizzle, you need to start over again, med to fm and try again, until you get no fizzles.<br>
<br>
On higher mana spells, you shouldn't notice a difference in the number of casts.  <br>
<br>
Non-specialization spells:  Here you should notice a difference.<br>
<br>
Test 1: <br>
Without the Focus item, cast nature's Touch, as many times as you can.  Record this number.<br>
<br>
Test 2:<br>
With the Focus item, cast nature's Touch as many times as you can.  Record this number.<br>
<br>
You should notice a difference in mana ending pools or just enough mana to cast one more nature's Touch.<br>
<br>
--------<br>
<br>
